 "title": "Climate Change and Global Food Security",
 "abstract": "Climate change and food security are integrally linked. How a changing climate affects a specific location, and the local effects on food security are, however, difficult to predict and place specific. Tracking climate risk and food security provides insight into current conditions, and provides a base level for future food security predictions under different climate scenarios. Ensuring food security for all is a social justice issue, and it is essential that climate adaptation measures consider the effects on agriculture, fisheries, livestock, food storage and distribution through a vulnerability lens.",
